## Status Icons

| Icon | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| ✅ | Approved (ready to merge or needs final approval) |
| 🔄 | Awaiting review |
| ⚠️ | Changes requested / blocking feedback |
| 📝 | Draft / still working on it |
| 🚫 | Blocked by external dependency |

## Flags

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--date YYYY-MM-DD` | Generate for specific date |
| `--yesterday` | Include yesterday's git activity |
| `--no-toggl` | Skip Toggl time tracking |
| `--no-linear` | Skip Linear issues |
| `--repos path` | Custom repos path (default: ~/code) |

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. **Don't list raw commits** - "refactor: move X" is meaningless without PR context
2. **Don't say "In Review"** - Say WHO is reviewing and WHAT the status is
3. **Don't trust Linear priority** - Ask the user what's actually high priority
4. **Don't forget PR links** - Teammates need to click through to help

